defaultPersons with disabilities have the same SR
defaultH needs as other people. Yet they often face barriers to information and services. The ignorance and attitudes of society and individuals, including health-care providers
default, raise most of these barriers -
default not the disabilities themselves. In fact, existing se
defaultrvices usually can be adapted easily to accommodate persons with disabilities. Increasing awareness is the first and biggest step. Beyond that, much can be accomplished through resourcefulness and involving persons with disabilities in programme design and
default monitoring.
